«»
The games and programs are usually stored in «c6»"ADF" «c7»format, quite similar
to «c6»"DMS", «c7»stored in «c6»"ZIP" «c7»archives. To use "ADF" on the Amiga is no
problem, as there exists programs for unpacking, packing and handling it.
You simply port the software over to the Amiga, unpack the "ADF" file like
you unpack a DMS file, and you are «c6»up and going.«»
«»
«c7»I'm quite excited about this emulator thing on the PC, but I can assume
